 \sin x = x + O(x^3) 
 (\pi - \frac{\pi}{2} x^2  + O(x^4))^3  = (\pi + O(x))^3  = \pi^3 + O(x)
 \begin{align}\sin(\pi \cos x) &= \sin(\pi - \frac{\pi}{2} x^2  + O(x^4)) \\ &= \pi - \frac{\pi}{2} x^2 + O(x^4) + O(\pi^3 + O(x)) = O(\pi^3) \end{align}
